some important doc attributes

document.URL
document.body
document.head
document.links


methods for grabbing elements from the DOM:
document.getElementById()
document.getElementByClassName()
document.getElementByTagName()  //for exampel the anchor tag
document.querySelector() gives the first object matching the css style selector
document.querySelectorAll() gives all the objects matching the css style selector

anything used for css can be passed into queryselector

-------lect2-----------

to edit styles, we've already seen we can use the .style tag. Now if we want to
edit ACTUAL HTML OR TEXT or attribute we can use different methods. If you want to
change the text.html content, or attributes you can use the following

myvariable.textContent - This returns just the text (so cannot chang something like style of the text)
myvariable.innerHTML - This returns the actual html (so we can use html tags to change style)
myvariable.getAttribute() - This returns the original attribute (takes the single parameter which is the attribute we want)
myvariable.setAttribute() - This allowed you to set an attribute (takes two parameter: the attribute and the value we want to set to it)


--------lect3-----------

listening to an event
syntax: myvariable.ddEventListener(event,func);
for exampel:var head=document.querySelector('h1')
            head.addEventListener("click",changeColor)
